{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "f9c34fd3-5a7c-4ba4-9e72-2c4c8e5ea101",
    "name": "Madhuban Backend API",
    "description": "Postman collection for Madhuban role-based task backend.\n\nStaff attendance: Staff → Attendance — GET status, POST check-in (selfie + GPS) and check-out (GPS) as multipart/form-data. Requires AWS S3 env for check-in uploads.\n\nStaff task photos: use Staff → Task photos (multipart). Flow: GET Tasks → POST before-photo → POST after-photo (creates TaskApproval for supervisor). Presigned upload and start/complete endpoints are not used.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Auth - Login (Admin)",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"{{adminEmail}}\",\n  \"password\": \"{{adminPassword}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "api",
                "auth",
                "login"
              ]
            }
          },
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
                  "  pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "let data = {};",
                  "try {",
                  "  data = pm.response.json();",
                  "} catch (e) {}",
                  "",
                  "if (data.token) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set(\"token\", data.token);",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "if (data.user && data.user.id) {",
                  "  pm.environment.set(\"adminUserId\", String(data.user.id));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "response": []
        },
